1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,480
Hello everyone and welcome back to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎回到EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,480 --> 00:00:07,800
We have an upper intermediate lesson for you today.
今天我们为大家准备了一节中高级课程。

3
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,220
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

4
00:00:09,220 --> 00:00:10,220
And my name is Catherine.
我是Catherine。

5
00:00:10,220 --> 00:00:13,660
So today we're talking about something that everyone who's ever lived away from home has
所以今天我们要聊的是每个曾经离家生活过的人都

6
00:00:13,660 --> 00:00:14,660
felt before.
感受过的事情。

7
00:00:14,660 --> 00:00:15,660
Right.
没错。

8
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:16,980
And that's the word we're going to preview today.
这就是我们今天要预览的单词。

9
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:17,980
The word is homesick.
这个词是“homesick”（想家的）。

10
00:00:17,980 --> 00:00:18,980
All right.
好的。

11
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:22,800
So let's take a look at that in today's language preview.
那么让我们在今天的语言预览中看看这个词。

12
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:23,800
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

13
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:24,800
All right.
好的。

14
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,800
So homesick.
所以，“homesick”。

15
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:28,760
If you feel homesick or you are homesick.
如果你感到想家或者你想家了。

16
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:32,920
Well, yeah, you could say I'm homesick right now.
嗯，是的，你可以说我现在想家了。

17
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:35,320
Or are you feeling homesick?
或者你感到想家吗？

18
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:38,960
So it's a word that means I miss my home.
所以这个词的意思是我想念我的家。

19
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,360
I miss my family.
我想念我的家人。

20
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:43,400
I'm far away or I haven't seen my family in a long time.
我离得很远，或者我很久没见到家人了。

21
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,440
And for some reason you just feel sad.
而且出于某种原因，你只是感到难过。

22
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:46,440
Okay.
好的。

23
00:00:46,440 --> 00:00:48,000
So it's a feeling.
所以这是一种感觉。

24
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,160
You feel a little bit depressed.
你感到有点沮丧。

25
00:00:49,160 --> 00:00:50,760
You feel sad because you're homesick.
你感到难过，因为你想家了。

26
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:51,760
Right.
没错。

27
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:52,760
Okay.
好的。

28
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:54,040
So this is what's happening today in our dialogue.
这就是我们今天对话中发生的事情。

29
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:59,440
So let's listen to it for the first time.
那么让我们第一次听一下。

30
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:05,440
Tom, how are you?
Tom，你好吗？

31
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,360
Hey, we missed you at the party last night.
嘿，我们昨晚在派对上没见到你。

32
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,360
Are you okay?
你还好吗？

33
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:10,000
I don't know.
我不知道。

34
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,800
I didn't really feel like going out.
我真的不太想出去。

35
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:14,400
I guess I'm feeling a little homesick.
我想我有点想家了。

36
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,400
Come on.
别这样。

37
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,400
We've been through this already.
我们已经经历过这个了。

38
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:20,720
Look, I know the adjustment was hard when you first got here, but we agree that you're
听着，我知道你刚来的时候适应很困难，但我们说好了你

39
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:22,840
going to try and deal with it.
要努力应对的。

40
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:24,000
I was.
我一直在努力。

41
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,040
It's just that the holidays are coming up and I won't be able to go home because I can't
只是假期快到了，我回不了家，因为我

42
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:29,800
afford the airfare.
买不起机票。

43
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:34,520
I'm just longing for some of the comforts of home, like my mom's cooking and being around
我只是渴望一些家的舒适，比如我妈妈的饭菜和

44
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,520
my family.
和家人在一起。

45
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:39,240
Yeah, it can get pretty lonely over the holidays.
是啊，假期里确实会感到挺孤独的。

46
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:43,240
When I first got here, I'd get depressed and nostalgic for anything that reminded me of
我刚来的时候，也会感到沮丧和怀旧，任何让我想起

47
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:44,240
home.
家的东西都会这样。

48
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:47,680
I almost let it get to me, but then I started going out, keeping myself busy.
我差点被它击垮，但后来我开始出去走走，让自己忙起来。

49
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:49,960
And before I knew it, I was used to it.
不知不觉中，我就习惯了。

50
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:53,520
I see what you mean, but I'm still bummed out.
我明白你的意思，但我还是很难过。

51
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:55,880
Okay, how does this sound?
好吧，这样怎么样？

52
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:58,840
Let's get you suited up and hit the dance club tonight.
我们今晚打扮一下，去舞厅跳舞吧。

53
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:04,200
I hear that an awesome DJ is playing and there will be a lot of pretty single girls there.
我听说有个很棒的DJ在打碟，而且那里会有很多漂亮的单身女孩。

54
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,960
You know, I could really go for that.
你知道吗，我还真想去。

55
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,640
You don't mind being my wingman for tonight?
你不介意今晚当我的僚机吧？

56
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:10,640
Not at all.
完全不介意。

57
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:11,880
It'll be fun.
会很好玩的。

58
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:13,880
It will be like a boys' night out.
就像个男生之夜。

59
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,400
Well, kind of.
嗯，差不多吧。

60
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,400
Great.
太好了。

61
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,480
I must warn you, though.
不过我得警告你。

62
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:21,040
Whatever happens, don't let me go on a drinking binge.
不管发生什么，别让我喝得酩酊大醉。

63
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:26,080
Trust me, it's not a pretty picture.
相信我，那可不是什么好看的画面。

64
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:30,320
All righty, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

65
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,500
So yeah, I guess he's very homesick.
所以，是的，我猜他非常想家。

66
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,500
Very homesick.
非常想家。

67
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:35,040
And his friend is really worried.
而且他的朋友真的很担心。

68
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,040
Yeah.
是啊。

69
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,640
But actually, I think this is common, right?
但实际上，我觉得这很常见，对吧？

70
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:40,720
To be homesick during the holidays, like Christmas, for example.
在假期里想家，比如圣诞节。

71
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:45,980
Oh, man, it's the worst during the holidays because you think of all the traditions and
哦，天哪，假期里最糟糕了，因为你会想起所有那些

72
00:02:45,980 --> 00:02:49,900
all the things that you normally do at home and you're not doing them.
你通常在家做的传统和事情，而你却做不了。

73
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,880
So this is something we're going to talk more about a little bit later on.
所以这是我们稍后会多聊一点的话题。

74
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:58,640
But let's take a look at some of the language that was used in Language Takeaway.
但让我们先看看“语言要点”中使用的一些语言。

75
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,580
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

76
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:02,620
This first one is key, right?
第一个是关键，对吧？

77
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:07,240
So when you move away from home or when you move to a new place, you have a period of
所以当你离开家或者搬到一个新地方时，你会有一段

78
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,280
adjustment.
适应期。

79
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:14,340
So adjustment is kind of finding the right balance or doing something so that you can
所以“adjustment”（适应）就是找到合适的平衡或做一些事情，以便你能

80
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,340
kind of feel comfortable.
感到舒适。

81
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:19,740
OK, so you have to adjust to your new life, life away from home.
好的，所以你必须适应你的新生活，远离家的生活。

82
00:03:19,740 --> 00:03:20,740
Or your new environment.
或者你的新环境。

83
00:03:20,740 --> 00:03:25,080
So many times people say, wow, moving to China must be a big adjustment.
所以很多时候人们会说，哇，搬到中国一定是个很大的适应过程。

84
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:29,560
So it means there's so many differences that it must take a long time to feel comfortable
所以这意味着有很多差异，需要很长时间才能再次感到舒适

85
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:30,560
again.
。

86
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:31,560
OK.
好的。

87
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,560
All right.
好的。

88
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,560
So that's adjustment.
这就是“adjustment”。

89
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,560
What else do we have?
我们还有什么？

90
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:38,960
Well, we've got this next phrase that's really important, I think, but often gets overlooked.
嗯，我们还有下一个短语，我觉得非常重要，但经常被忽视。

91
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:41,960
We say the comforts of home, right?
我们说“the comforts of home”（家的舒适），对吧？

92
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:42,960
Comforts of home.
家的舒适。

93
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,680
So comfort's pretty easy, right?
所以“comfort”很容易理解，对吧？

94
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,680
Feeling comfortable.
感到舒适。

95
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,840
So you have comfort.
所以你有舒适。

96
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:51,220
But the comforts of home are things that are different with every person.
但“家的舒适”是因人而异的。

97
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:54,440
But those are things that you have at your home or your childhood home or your parents'
但那些是你家里、童年家里或父母

98
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:57,120
home that make you feel good and feel happy.
家里让你感觉良好和快乐的东西。

99
00:03:57,120 --> 00:04:00,240
So they're not only physical things or objects, right?
所以它们不仅仅是实物或物品，对吧？

100
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:04,120
They can be like your mom's cooking or maybe even just spending time with your family.
它们可以是像你妈妈的饭菜，或者只是和家人在一起的时间。

101
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:08,360
Right, or reading the newspaper with your dad or things that you're used to that you
没错，或者和爸爸一起看报纸，或者你习惯做但

102
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,760
don't have anymore.
不再拥有的东西。

103
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,160
And so those are the comforts of home.
所以那些就是家的舒适。

104
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:14,040
I could say, Marco, do you miss the comforts of home in Ecuador?
我可以说，Marco，你想念厄瓜多尔家里的舒适吗？

105
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:17,080
I mean, do you have anything that's really...
我是说，你有什么特别……

106
00:04:17,080 --> 00:04:18,080
Of course, of course.
当然，当然。

107
00:04:18,080 --> 00:04:22,080
I think one of the main things is actually not living in the city because I used to live
我觉得主要的一点其实是不住在城市里，因为我以前

108
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:25,520
in the valley a little bit further away and kind of almost countryside.
住在山谷里，稍微远一点，有点像乡村。

109
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:28,280
So that's one of the comforts of home that I miss.
所以那是我想念的家的舒适之一。

110
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:31,080
Oh, you're making me nostalgic and I've never even been.
哦，你让我感到怀旧了，我都没去过那里。

111
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:32,080
All right.
好的。

112
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,720
Well, this is our next word, actually.
嗯，这实际上是我们下一个词。

113
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:34,720
Right, nostalgic.
没错，“nostalgic”（怀旧的）。

114
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,720
Nostalgic.
怀旧的。

115
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:36,720
It's a feeling.
这是一种感觉。

116
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:39,320
I'm feeling nostalgic or he's just really nostalgic.
我感到怀旧，或者他只是非常怀旧。

117
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:45,440
And so to be nostalgic is to kind of think about a time before or think positively about
所以怀旧就是回想以前的日子，或者积极看待

118
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,140
something that you experienced before.
你以前经历过的事情。

119
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:49,300
So it's not usually a bad thing.
所以通常不是坏事。

120
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:50,960
It's never a bad thing.
从来不是坏事。

121
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:54,120
Nostalgia is a good, warm, fond memory of something.
怀旧是对某件事美好、温暖、珍贵的回忆。

122
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,560
Of something from your past.
对你过去某件事的回忆。

123
00:04:55,560 --> 00:05:00,440
So you start thinking of something from your past that maybe brings nice, warm feelings,
所以你开始回想过去的一些事，那些可能带来美好、温暖感觉的事，

124
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:04,400
maybe a little bit sad because you miss those times, but it's usually thinking about the
也许有点伤感，因为你怀念那些时光，但通常是在回忆

125
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,400
past.
过去。

126
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,400
Right.
对。

127
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,400
So I have nostalgia for my childhood.
所以我怀念我的童年。

128
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:12,280
I loved, you know, summers in Chicago and it was hot and the kids would play in the
我喜欢，你知道，芝加哥的夏天，天气很热，孩子们在

129
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:17,200
sprinkler and I had my dog and you know, it's a happy feeling.
洒水器里玩耍，我养了我的狗，你知道，那是一种快乐的感觉。

130
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,200
Right.
对。

131
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,840
So nostalgia would be the noun and nostalgic would be the adjective.
所以 nostalgia 是名词，nostalgic 是形容词。

132
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:21,840
Exactly.
没错。

133
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:22,840
All right.
好的。

134
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:27,600
And our last word for today on Language Takeaway is bummed out.
今天“语言小贴士”的最后一个词是 bummed out。

135
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,600
Bummed out.
Bummed out。

136
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,600
I'm bummed out.
我很沮丧。

137
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,600
We've got another feeling here.
我们又有了另一种感觉。

138
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:32,520
So we're all full of feelings today.
所以我们今天充满了各种感觉。

139
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,240
Bummed out is a sad feeling.
Bummed out 是一种悲伤的感觉。

140
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:38,840
So to be bummed is kind of slang and it means to be sad.
所以 to be bummed 是一种俚语，意思是感到悲伤。

141
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:39,840
Okay.
好的。

142
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:40,840
Or disappointed.
或者失望。

143
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:41,840
Disappointed.
失望。

144
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:44,360
So you come into the office, Marco, and you look a little tired.
所以你走进办公室，Marco，看起来有点累。

145
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,360
I said, are you okay?
我说，你还好吗？

146
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,120
Are you bummed out about something?
你是不是因为什么事而沮丧？

147
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:51,360
I can say, yeah, I lost my wallet last night so I'm really bummed out.
我可以说，是啊，我昨晚丢了钱包，所以真的很沮丧。

148
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:53,200
Or something like that.
或者类似的情况。

149
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:56,720
So yeah, you feel bummed out when something bad or sad happens.
所以是的，当坏事或伤心事发生时，你会感到沮丧。

150
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,720
Right.
对。

151
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,720
All right.
好的。

152
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:05,240
So let's move on now to a couple of different phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在我们进入“流利度提升”部分，看看几个不同的短语。

153
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,240
Fluency Builder.
流利度提升。

154
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,240
All right.
好的。

155
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:10,880
This first one is something that you often say to old friends or family.
第一个是你经常对老朋友或家人说的话。

156
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:14,920
You know, when you're friends with someone, they go through periods of happiness and sadness.
你知道，当你和某人做朋友时，他们会经历快乐和悲伤的时期。

157
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:18,960
And so when someone's going through a down period again, you say, oh, we've been through
所以当某人再次经历低谷时，你会说，哦，我们之前已经

158
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:19,960
this already.
经历过这个了。

159
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,800
We've been through this already.
我们之前已经经历过这个了。

160
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:25,240
Or you know, when you're giving someone advice and they never take your advice, you say,
或者你知道，当你给别人建议，但他们从不采纳时，你会说，

161
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,880
